<darktable_style version="1.0"><info><name>lens_correction</name><description>Parameterized lens correction via darktable's lens module (#95). Provides 10 manual-override magnitude axes for distortion / TCA / vignette correction. NOTE: this entry's photographic effect requires the lensfun identifier strings (camera/lens) and shooting metadata (focal/aperture/distance) to be populated — without those, the lensfun auto-correction can't fire. EXIF auto-binding for these fields is tracked as a follow-up. Until then, this entry is most useful as a starting point for users who manually authored a lens-correction dtstyle in darktable's GUI and want to override the strength sliders.</description></info><style><plugin><num>0</num><module>10</module><operation>lens</operation><op_params></op_params><enabled>1</enabled><blendop_params>gz11eJxjYIAACQYYOOHEgAZY0QWAgBGLGANDgz0Ej1Q+dcF/IADRAGpyHQU=</blendop_params><blendop_version>14</blendop_version><multi_priority>0</multi_priority><multi_name></multi_name><multi_name_hand_edited>0</multi_name_hand_edited></plugin></style></darktable_style>
